<HOME_STRUCTURE>
- The 'home/' directory MUST contain all Home Manager related code, organized for clarity and modularity.
- All user-specific host configurations should reside under 'home/hosts/'.
- All Home Manager modules should reside under 'home/modules/'.
- The main Home Manager entrypoint should be 'home/home.nix'.
- The intended directory structure for 'home/' is as follows:

home/
├── hosts/
│   ├── <host1>/
│   │   └── default.nix
│   └── <host2>/
│       └── default.nix
├── modules/
│   ├── core/
│   ├── dev/
│   ├── gaming/
│   ├── programs/
│   ├── session/
│   ├── shell/
│   ├── tools/
│   └── ui/
└── home.nix

- All import paths in home-related configuration files MUST be updated to reflect this structure.
- This structure is intended to maximize maintainability, clarity, and modularity for Home Manager configurations.
</HOME_STRUCTURE>
